{"key":"processedPost-13080759","value":{"id":13080759,"first":13080204,"last":13080882,"when":1282362830,"utime":"08/21/10 06:53 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>Pandor said:</strong><br />Well I had originally planned on just shotguns. A few of them. But then it was brought to my attention that when you live in a climate that is this dry, a mere shotgun will not do. </blockquote><br />Not true.&nbsp; My climate is drier than yours.(as a mod, I see your IP)<br />First, in extremely dry climates, you should run a humidifier in your house.&nbsp; I run one all winter up here, because it's less than ten percent humidity.&nbsp; A humidifier makes you healthier, lowers your heating and cooling bills, and keeps your skin from drying out.<br />Second, cakes do poorly in mini-greenhouses.&nbsp; They really need the fresh air exchange and 95% and greater humidity.&nbsp; Save your mini-greenhouse for when you move up to bulk substrates.<br />Third, you shouldn't pipe a humidifier in to a greenhouse.&nbsp; I've posted for a decade that it will fry your humidifier in short order.&nbsp; Most members here who have disregarded that advice have a pile of broken down humidifiers in their junk pile.&nbsp; <br />For a mini-greenhouse, simply take a knife and cut a bunch of slits in it, and then set the cool mist humidifier on the floor so it can shoot straight up.&nbsp; Set it <i>beside</i> the shelves, not on a bottom shelf.&nbsp; If it's on a bottom shelf, the mist will hit the shelf above and rain back down.&nbsp; The mist needs to be able to shoot nearly to the top of the greenhouse.<br />For cakes, use a <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">shotgun terrarium</a> or two.&nbsp; If your humidity indoors is less than 25%, simply run a humidifier in the room in which the terrarium is located.&nbsp; It will make you feel better and also lower your utility bills, since humid air has more thermal mass and will hold heat and cool better.<br />RR","title":"Re: check this greenhouse out"}}